  m_Name: coleoptera
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::WordInfo
  words:
  - Coleoptera
  - coleopteras
  info: 'Coleoptera is an order of sheathed winged insects. Insects such as beetles
    and weevils comprise this order. Through the wide variety of beetles and weevils,
    this order is one of the largest in the animal kingdom. Insects in this order
    undergo complete metamorphosis. While beetles are often considered pests, beetles
    play a useful role as organic matter decomposers and recyclers.


    Source:
    https://genent.cals.ncsu.edu/insect-identification/order-coleoptera/'
  image: {fileID: 2800000, guid: fcb8a81b5afbc7640b9998d9ff5153fb, type: 3}
